即使下雨，我也要去上课
你是怎么去学校的？我是坐地铁去学校的。> S. + shì + method／time／place + V. + O. + de
你是什么时候开始打篮球的？我是十岁开始打篮球的。> S. + shì + method／time／place + V. + O. + de
你是在哪儿学书法的？我是在交通大学学书法的。> S. + shì + method／time／place + V. + O. + de
即使明天下雨，我也要去学校。> 即使…，…也… Even if, Even though. The conjunction phrase ‘even if’ is used to say that if something is the case or not, the result is the same. The former clause is a supposition, and ‘yě’ is placed between the subject and verb in the latter one.
即使书法很难，我也打算学。> 即使…，…也… Even if, Even though. The conjunction phrase ‘even if’ is used to say that if something is the case or not, the result is the same. The former clause is a supposition, and ‘yě’ is placed between the subject and verb in the latter one.
这两件衣服，你想买哪一件？
手机丢了，我只能自认倒霉，再买一个新的了。
